metadata.name: Insolence
metadata.description:
Let's talk about the shadow side of man. 
Nun. A very controversial image. After all, behind any light, hides a shadow. 
And so in my painting I let it come out. 
Boldness in all its manifestations, where she shows her gesture to society and the frames. Where she just allows herself to be a sexy hottie. 
Where she allowed herself to own money. Sitting on the golden toilet with her panties down, also in protest.
She calls for her shadow to be accepted and heard, for it is also part of her identity.
In the background we see paintings of different directions. There is a cathedral, and on the other side there are suits and a crown as a sign of power. 
There are inscriptions that may seem crude, but after all, everything is relative. 
And with modern art we add charm to the picture. 
Let yourself be you.

Acrylic and canvas
